provisions.content:
1. Sales slips for approved goods shall show-
                (a) the name of the visitor;
                 (b) the foreign address of the visitor;
                 (c) the visitor's address m Jamaica;
                 (4 the date of the sale;
                 (e) the name of the carrier and the flight number, or the name
                      of the ship and the cabin number;
THE TOURIST (DUTY-FREE: SHOPPING SYSTEM REGULATIONS, 1975
                       THIRD SCHEDULE, contd.
          (f) the date and time of departure;
          (g) the port or place from which the visitor is leaving;
          (h) the description of the goods;
          (9 the quantity of the goods;
          0') the unit price of the goods;
           ( k ) the value of the goods;
            (I) a declaration Q be signed by the visitor stating that he
                   is neither domiciled nor ordinarily resident in Jamaica, and
                  that the goods purchased will be exported;
          (m) any of the following--
                       (i) the visitor's visa number or passport number and
                           its country of origin;
                      (ii) landing card number (if numbered);
                     (iii) the number of the return travel ticket, quoting carrier,
                           date and place of issue of ticket;
                     (iv) the number of the social security card or any other
                            entry document by which the visitor was landed in
                            Jamaica;
            in) the signature of the tourist (duty-free) shop operator or his
                   duly appointed agent or representative; and
            ( L ) the signature of the Customs officer who shall also certify,
                   where necessary, the production of satisfactory travel docu-
                  ments by the visitor.
